-level-shifters-for-timing-critical-signals","target":"74hct-buffers-are-purpose-built-3v3-to-5v-level-shifters-for-timing-critical-signals","line":57},{"title":"i2s-timing-requirements-make-level-shifting-a-non-solution-for-voltage-incompatible-mcus","target":"i2s-timing-requirements-make-level-shifting-a-non-solution-for-voltage-incompatible-mcus","line":58},{"title":"wireless-modules-are-overwhelmingly-3v3-making-level-shifting-the-default","target":"wireless-modules-are-overwhelmingly-3v3-making-level-shifting-the-default","line":59},{"title":"eda-fundamentals","target":"eda-fundamentals","line":62},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":63},{"title":"communication","target":"communication","line":64}],"metadata":{"description":"The correct level shifter for a given pin pair depends primarily on signal topology (open-drain vs push-pull) and clock speed, not on the voltage pair — the same 3.3V-to-5V translation demands different shifter architectures for I2C versus SPI versus NeoPixel data, and voltage compatibility alone does not constrain the choice","type":"claim","source":"docs/parts/hw-221-8-channel-bidirectional-level-shifter-bss138-based.md","confidence":"proven","topics":["[[eda-fundamentals]]","[[shields]]","[[communication]]"],"related_components":["hw-221-level-shifter","txs0108e-level-shifter","74hct245-buffer"]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"knowledge/signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection.md"},"smart_blocks:knowledge/signal-topology-not-voltage-alone-determines-level-shifter-selection.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"11m6ox2","at":1776207914398},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.09340408,0.02206248,0.0142367,-0.01847999,-0.02792692,0.01789374,-0.02459408,0.05648513,0.01315743,-0.00226201,0.05894767,-0.06456921,0.01028455,0.04334584,0.02782624,0.00112727,-0.0379047,-0.0066712,0.09096711,0.06767891,0.09819671,-0.06166097,-0.03050918,0.00493863,0.06842